article.headline: Baylor 90, Angelo State 65
article.story: WACO, Texas (AP) -- Kevin Rogers scored a career-high 21 points and pulled down eight rebounds for Baylor, which beat Angelo State 90-65 on Saturday night in the season opener for both teams. Tim Bush added 17 points for the Bears, while Aaron Bruce had 11 points, six rebounds and six assists. Henry Dugat added 11 points. Josh Lomers, starting in the place of injured center Mamadou Diene, had 10 points and seven rebounds. Marcus Hubbard of Angelo State led all scorers with 29 points and six rebounds. Former Baylor guard Turner Phipps scored 17 points for the Rams.
